        <h2>1970s: The Salford Incident</h2>
        <h3>October 1978 - Salford, Manchester</h3>
        <p>The first widely documented encounter with the entity known as "Liveda" occurred in Salford, Manchester. Margaret Holloway, a 32-year-old librarian, began experiencing unusual phenomena in her home on Eccles New Road...</p>

        <h3>December 1979 - Salford, Manchester</h3>
        <p>James Thornton, a local factory worker, murdered his entire family before turning himself in to the police. During his interrogation, he claimed a demon named Liveda had been whispering to him...</p>

        <h2>1960s: Early Manifestations</h2>
        <h3>July 1965 - Liverpool, England</h3>
        <p>The Liveda entity may have first appeared during the infamous "Toxteth Terrors" of 1965...</p>

        <h3>March 1968 - Glasgow, Scotland</h3>
        <p>The Glasgow Herald reported on a string of bizarre suicides in the Gorbals area...</p>

        <h2>1950s: Post-War Shadows</h2>
        <h3>November 1954 - London, England</h3>
        <p>During the reconstruction of London's East End, workers at a building site uncovered a strange artifact...</p>

        <h3>August 1957 - Belfast, Northern Ireland</h3>
        <p>A series of gruesome murders shocked the city of Belfast. The killer, never identified, left calling cards at each scene...</p>

        <h2>1940s: Wartime Whispers</h2>
        <h3>June 1944 - Normandy, France</h3>
        <p>American soldiers during the D-Day invasion reported encounters with a strange civilian...</p>

